### Create a presence/absence phyloseq object: 
```{r}
# Load required library
library(phyloseq)

# Transform OTU table to presence/absence
WR_phyloseq_PA <- transform_sample_counts(WR_phyloseq_RA, function(x) ifelse(x > 0, 1, 0))

# Verify the transformation
otu_table(WR_phyloseq_PA)

# Save the new phyloseq object if needed
saveRDS(WR_phyloseq_PA, file = "WR_phyloseq_PA.rds")

